# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OpenDocViewer â€” .gitignore
# Purpose: Keep the repo clean and deterministic while developing with Vite + React
# and running the optional Express log server. Comments here are intentionally verbose
# so future maintainers (human or AI) know why each pattern exists.
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Node dependency tree (reproducible from package.json)
node_modules/

# Vite production output
dist/

# Vite/ESBuild caches (harmless if committed, but no reason to)
.vite/
.eslintcache

# Operating system noise
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# Editors / IDEs
.vscode/
.idea/
*.iml

# Local environment files (never commit real secrets)
# Keep an example file (e.g., .env.example) under source control instead.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Log server output (runtime data)
# We intentionally keep the logs/ directory (for convenience),
# but ignore rotating log files within it. If you want to keep the folder
# in the repo tree, you can add a logs/.gitkeep file.
logs/
!logs/.gitkeep

# Generated documentation (JSDoc)
# By default we generate docs/ locally. If you publish docs via GitHub Pages,
# consider using a dedicated branch or an explicit workflow instead of committing here.
docs/

# Test coverage outputs (if enabled later)
coverage/
.nyc_output/

# Package manager debug logs
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
pnpm-debug.log*
lerna-debug.log*

# Patch/backup files
*.orig
*.rej
*.bak
*.tmp

# Yarn PnP (not used here, but safe to ignore if someone experiments locally)
.pnp.*
.yarn/*
!.yarn/patches
!.yarn/plugins
!.yarn/releases
!.yarn/sdks
!.yarn/versions

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# IMPORTANT: We intentionally DO NOT ignore package-lock.json by default.
# If you decide to track a lockfile for reproducible installs across CI/clients,
# keep it committed. If you choose not to track a lockfile, add it here explicitly.
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
